news.title: China Evergrande Group to hire more advisers to help deal with debt
news.para: Evergrande is the world's most-indebted property company with more than $300 billion in liabilities, including nearly $20 billion of international bonds all deemed to be in default after a run of missed payments late last year.

news.title: Birla Corporation inaugurates Rs 2,744-crore Mukutban cement plant
news.para: The greenfield project of RCCPL Private Ltd, a wholly owned subsidiary of the cement maker, takes the group's total installed capacity to 20 million tonne per annum.

news.title: Gurugram: About 1,000 illegal jhuggis near Golf Gourse Road razed
news.para: A day after sealing 10 commercial establishments running from residential plots in the colony, the department targetted unauthorised jhuggis constructed despite ban on construction in the colony.
